article.headline: UC Irvine 57, Princeton 55
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Adam Parada's 4-foot hook shot with 1.8 seconds remaining lifted UC Irvine to a 57-55 victory over Princeton on Friday in the opening round of the McCaffrey Classic. Stanislav Zuzak and Mike Efevberha scored 12 points apiece to lead UC Irvine (3-2). Efevberha added the winning assist, passing to Parada after penetrating the defense. Scott Greenman scored 14 points and Judson Wallace added 13 for Princeton (3-1), which made 11 three-pointers. Greenman finished 4 of 5 from beyond the stripe.
